question
Write a function maxMin that takes an array arr as arguments 
and returns an array containing the maximum and minimum value: [max, min]. If the array is empty, return [].
Example:
function maxMin ([3, 4, 8, 1]) should return [8, 1];
function maxMin ([7, 7]) must return [7, 7];
function maxMin ([2]) should return [2, 2];
function maxMin ([]) must return [];


solution:

function maxMin(arr){
  let max = Math.max(...arr);
  let min = Math.min(...arr);
  if(arr.length === 0) return [];
  return [max, min];
}
